Since this is a tab for a single guitar some aspects of the complete arrangement must be taken into count, and therefore D9/F# sounds a bit better. Instead of playing Fmaj7 like it's described above there's a slightly more comfortable way to play it and it goes like this: Fmaj7 x 3 3 2 1 0 However, if you play it like this you'll no longer have the descending bass line (G-F#-F) on the 6th string.
